result.name: Infiniti C

reviews.text:
Infiniti C is famous for their delicious vegan friendly food, especially cakes. Happen to be in the hood during a long weekend, and I decided to give their cakes a try.

The cafe was quite busy on a Saturday evening. It was actually full when I visited, and I was lucky to get a seat. Solo diner luck I would say.

There were quite a variety of vegan cakes of the day. I had a difficult time deciding which one to try as all of them looked so delicious. I got this Passion Fruit Chocolate Cake at the end, as I felt like the passion fruit would be refreshing for a warm evening.

And it definitely did not disappoint! Refreshing passion fruit sauce and crunchy chocolate nibs. The cream was so smooth and enjoyable! As for the cake itself - the dark layers were spongy and the light layer was a very delicious mousse like layer, so delicious!

One more good vegan cake place found!
This place is lovely! Their food is super fresh and tasty. It's a great breakfast spot and it's a great addition to the neighborhood. Clearly something different than other coffee places.

Another perfect fine coffee in Sai Wan area. You won’t regret for visiting. 

Do try their coffee and don’t forget their gluten free pastries and cakes. The Earl Grey Chiffon Cake is definitely a must try.

High quality healthy food and desserts and probably the only Cafe in Hong Kong to serve tiger nut milk! Really enjoyed the Black Swan Latte and tofu toast for breakfast. Had an extra oat milk latte and made some space for the Keto tiramisu cake which tastes much better than it sounds. Would've given 5 stars if they indicated the allergens on the menu because I had lactose by accident..
Sooo good!! One of the best coffee shops around!!

夢幻蛋糕店，每天供應人手做的西式甜品，亦常常有新品種，配合時令的食材，常常有驚喜，做得很细緻漂亮，味道很好，打咭一流，達到做的用心，食的開心!

靠近地鐵，坐位寬大很舒適，主打無麩質
**推薦: 燕麥蔓越莓曲奇餅乾 (超鬆軟超香超好吃，大讚)
Close to the subway, the seating is spacious and comfortable, gluten-free
**recommended: Oatmeal Cranberry Cookies
